## 📋 QA Findings & Security Recommendations

### 🟡 Informational Findings

> [!NOTE]
> **No Rate Limiting / Account Lockout** (TC_NEG_013)
> 
> 5 consecutive failed login attempts were made with no lockout, CAPTCHA, or delay.
> **Recommendation:** Implement rate limiting (e.g., max 5 attempts per IP per minute) or a CAPTCHA challenge after 3 failures.

> [!NOTE]
> **Email Confirmation Required for Login** (TC_POS_001)
>
> The app uses Supabase Auth with mandatory email verification. New registrations cannot log in until the email is confirmed. This is expected Supabase behaviour but should be surfaced with a clearer UI message like *"Please check your inbox to confirm your email before logging in."*

> [!NOTE]
> **Generic Error Message** (TC_NEG_007)
>
> The app correctly returns a single generic message `"Invalid login credentials"` for both wrong email and wrong password. This is **excellent** for security as it prevents user enumeration. ✅

### 🟢 Positive Security Findings

- ✅ **Password is masked** — no shoulder-surfing risk
- ✅ **SQL injection safely rejected** — no auth bypass or server crash
- ✅ **XSS payload not executed** — no script injection vulnerability
- ✅ **No stack traces leaked** in error messages
- ✅ **Generic errors** prevent user enumeration attacks
- ✅ **Email is case-normalised** — consistent UX

---

## 🚀 How to Run

```bash
# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Run all 30 tests (headed — browser visible)
cd qa_tests
python run_tests.py

# Run headless (CI-friendly)
python run_tests.py --headless

# Run a specific suite
python run_tests.py --suite ui
python run_tests.py --suite positive
python run_tests.py --suite negative

# Run directly with pytest
python -m pytest tests/ -v -s
```

---

## 📊 HTML Report

An interactive HTML report is generated at:
`qa_tests/reports/final_report.html`

Open it in any browser to see:
- Individual test statuses with pass/fail indicators
- Captured `print()` output for each test
- Full tracebacks for any failing tests
- Duration per test
